Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.46,0:02:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,- C'mon! You didn't even hear us out!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.75,0:02:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,- Our orders are clear! The\NMistral-Atlas border is closed!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.29,0:02:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,- Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.08,0:02:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,- Have a good day!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.13,0:02:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,- But...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.67,0:02:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,- A good day!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.92,0:02:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,- Hey, if you don't wanna believe
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.33,0:02:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that I'm friends with Ironwood
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.00,0:02:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,- General Ironwood!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.67,0:02:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yeah, General Ironwood, then fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.46,0:02:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But look, we have Weiss Schnee with us
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.58,0:02:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and we're trying to get her home safely.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.42,0:02:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,- Approach!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.08,0:03:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,- Very well! You may speak with our
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.88,0:03:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,commanding officer.\NWe will fetch her at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.38,0:03:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}- Hup-hup-hup-hup-hup!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.50,0:03:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,- Hup-hup-hup-hup-hup!\N-Atlas! Atlas! Atlas!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.63,0:03:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,- They were kind of...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.17,0:03:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,- Super weird?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.33,0:03:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,- Huh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.79,0:03:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,- Hmmmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.92,0:03:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,- What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.58,0:03:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,- Well I, may know this\Ncommanding officer.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.17,0:03:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,- That's good isn't it?\NIf she's your friend
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.04,0:03:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,then maybe she'd be\Nmore willing to help us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.54,0:03:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,- I wouldn't exactly call us..."friends".
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.63,0:03:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,- Acquaintances?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.50,0:03:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,- Not quite.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.50,0:03:35.33,Default,,0,0,0,,- Colleagues?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.33,0:03:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,- Warmer.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.50,0:03:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,- Enemies?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.58,0:03:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,- That's the one!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.54,0:03:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,- Wait, what?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.63,0:03:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- Oh, yes. I come through here about once
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.96,0:03:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,every ten years to get my\Neyes checked up in Atlas.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.21,0:03:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You bring outside cashews on one flight,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.00,0:03:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and suddenly you're\Nplaced on the additional
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.58,0:03:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,screening list for life!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.54,0:03:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,- You've gotta be kidding me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.71,0:03:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,- Now, now. Let's not give up hope yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.79,0:04:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe she's dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.46,0:04:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,- Introducing!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.63,0:04:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,- Special operative!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.83,0:04:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,- Caroline Cordovin!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.04,0:04:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,- Witch.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.71,0:04:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,- She-devil.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.75,0:04:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,- Hm, I've seen you've chosen larger
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.54,0:04:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,contraband to smuggle this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.08,0:04:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,- Oh, Cordo. You know they\Nsay time changes people,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.67,0:04:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,but I see you've still\Ngot that stick right up-
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.75,0:04:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,- H-hello! Miss, uh, Cordovin.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.04,0:04:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Ruby Rose, and I was wondering
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.42,0:04:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,if you would hear us out about-
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.75,0:04:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,- I've already heard what your
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.83,0:04:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,other little friends had to say, Miss Rose.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.96,0:04:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing back here??
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.13,0:04:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I told you to leave!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.96,0:04:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,- And I told you we\Nwouldn't rest until you let us through!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.29,0:05:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,- Nice to see again as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.21,0:05:04.33,Default,,0,0,0,,- You civilians are clearly incapable
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.33,0:05:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,of comprehending the importance
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.50,0:05:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,of our mission here in Argus.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.13,0:05:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So allow me to say this\Nslowly, with smaller words:
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.42,0:05:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,This base, that relay tower,\Nthe very safety of Argus
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.42,0:05:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,are all gifts from the\Nglorious Kingdom of Atlas.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.83,0:05:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And it is my duty to uphold them, as only
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.75,0:05:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I have the wit and tenacity for such a task.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.38,0:05:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,- Such wit!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.54,0:05:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,- Such tenacity!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.21,0:05:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,- Or maybe Atlas just wanted to get you
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.08,0:05:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,as far from the kingdom as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.75,0:05:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,- You're just like the rest\Nof these Argus ingrates!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.13,0:05:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,This city wouldn't even\Nbe here if it weren't
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.13,0:05:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,for our Atlesian ancestors, and
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.00,0:05:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,what do we get in return? The entire world
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.96,0:05:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,is ready to put a knife to our throats!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.71,0:05:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,- Please, we know your kingdom had nothing
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.92,0:05:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,to do with the fall of\NBeacon -- we were there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.79,0:05:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,- No one's happy about the Atlas borders
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.58,0:06:01.58,Default,,0,0,0,,or embargo, but I know General\NIronwood is just worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.58,0:06:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's why we need to talk to-
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.17,0:06:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,- The General is no\Ncoward! Atlas is strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.96,0:06:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,If all the kingdoms plan\Nto make us their enemy,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.50,0:06:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,then so be it! Atlas will prevail!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.75,0:06:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,- Atlas will prevail!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.79,0:06:16.37,Default,,0,0,0,,- Do you guys seriously have to do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.21,0:06:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,- If Miss Schnee has\Ntruly come to her senses
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.50,0:06:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and wishes to return to her family,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.63,0:06:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,then of course the Atlas\Nmilitary will escort her home.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.04,0:06:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But the Kingdom will not be responsible
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.46,0:06:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,for her "friends" of\Nquestionable character.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.63,0:06:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,- What's that supposed to mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.67,0:06:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,- It means we're done here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.25,0:06:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,- Oh yeah? Well you're face looks...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.17,0:06:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Like a big dumb boot!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.17,0:06:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,- Way to show her, Nora.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.42,0:06:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,- I don't...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.71,0:06:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Ruby] Weiss.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.42,0:06:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,- I told you we wouldn't
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.58,0:07:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,leave your side for a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.71,0:07:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll find a way to Atlas. Together.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.79,0:07:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,- So, where are we going now?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.29,0:07:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yeah...what's the plan?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.96,0:07:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,- The plan? The plan\Njust got shut on our face
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.75,0:07:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,three times over. I'm going for a drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.17,0:07:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- Uncle Qrow, I really think we should
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.96,0:07:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,try and come up with something...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.25,0:07:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,...together.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.46,0:07:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,- What's his problem? It's\Nnot your fault we can't go on.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.13,0:07:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,- If he's gonna be a jerk then we'll just
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.67,0:07:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,come up with something without him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.38,0:07:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, we've got Ozpin with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.67,0:07:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,He usually knows what to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.71,0:07:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.25,0:07:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,- Jaune!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.08,0:07:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,- Everything we did was for nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.54,0:07:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Blake] That's not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.67,0:07:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,- Really? Cuz it sure does sound like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.58,0:07:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,- I, um....
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.33,0:08:00.91,Default,,0,0,0,,- If Salem can't be killed, then
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.92,0:08:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,how are we supposed to win this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.83,0:08:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Jaune] Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.67,0:08:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,- Great plan everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.58,0:08:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,- Look, none of this is great, we know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.13,0:08:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But we're not the bad guys here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.33,0:08:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,- Are we sure about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.04,0:08:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,- What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.54,0:08:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,- He's in your head, isn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.38,0:08:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you already know about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.21,0:08:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,- He didn't know any of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.83,0:08:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,- How much longer can we even trust him?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.67,0:08:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,- Jaune!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.46,0:08:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,- How do we even know it's really him?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.25,0:08:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What if we've been talking\Nto that liar this whole time?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.17,0:08:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,- Jaune!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.67,0:09:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,- Is he gonna be okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.38,0:09:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,- I don't know!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.58,0:09:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,- I think it would be best if\Nwe had some time to ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.67,0:09:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,- Maybe we could all use some space.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.96,0:09:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,- Come on, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.25,0:09:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.46,0:09:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,- You know, I came out\Nhere to avoid the yelling.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.54,0:09:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,- Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.00,0:09:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The others went\Nto get food for tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.21,0:09:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,- Why not go with them?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.25,0:10:00.25,Default,,0,0,0,,- I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.92,0:10:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.58,0:10:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What do I tell Jaune and his team
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.25,0:10:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,when we don't even have a plan?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.63,0:10:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Qrow's out drinking,\NOzpin hasn't come back
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.96,0:10:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and even if he did, I don't\Nknow if I could trust him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.29,0:10:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's always Jinn, but we only have
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.71,0:10:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,one more question we can ask her.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.46,0:10:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel like I'm letting everyone down.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.63,0:10:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,- You know, you don't give\Nyourself enough credit.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.00,0:10:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,- Oh, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.17,0:10:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,- That wasn't a compliment.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.79,0:10:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,- Uh...what?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.92,0:10:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,- If I have to explain it to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.63,0:10:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,it will just defeat the purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.17,0:10:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you're tired of\Nnot knowing anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.29,0:10:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,how about we discuss those eyes of yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.79,0:10:48.83,Default,,0,0,0,,- Oh! Yes ma'am, I would be honored!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.38,0:10:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,- Sit back down, for Pete's sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.38,0:10:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's start with what\Nyou do know. Tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.33,0:11:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,- Uh... silver-eyed people are supposed
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.79,0:11:04.87,Default,,0,0,0,,to be legendary warriors.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.25,0:11:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.96,0:11:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And at the Fall of Beacon, I turned
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.67,0:11:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,a giant Wyvern into stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.58,0:11:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,- Oh, boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.38,0:11:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,- Look, if I already knew everything
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.00,0:11:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't be asking for help.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.88,0:11:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yelling.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.92,0:11:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not your fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.71,0:11:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I had my father to teach me, and even he
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.79,0:11:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't have all the\Nanswers. But what he told me
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.67,0:11:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,makes sense, given what I've seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.96,0:11:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,- Was he a Huntsman too?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.42,0:11:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,- It wasn't really an official\Ntitle back in his day.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.63,0:11:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I only knew him as an old\Nsolider, and an excellent teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.83,0:11:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I never attended one of those\Nfancy academies of yours,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.83,0:11:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,but I scored higher on\Nthe license exam than
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.17,0:11:56.13,Default,,0,0,0,,any other Huntsman or Huntress that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.83,0:11:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,- You must've been proud.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.38,0:12:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,- He would've scolded me for showing off.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.29,0:12:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,He'd never been able to find much
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.88,0:12:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,information about our abilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.67,0:12:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Just legends of warriors\Nwhose eyes shown like mirrors,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.13,0:12:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,reflecting the light of\Nthe world onto darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.17,0:12:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,He found so little, in fact,\Nthat it made him cautious.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.17,0:12:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,How could such powerful\Nbloodlines be so rare?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.00,0:12:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Unless, something was actively\Nseeking to destroy them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.67,0:12:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,- Salem.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.38,0:12:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,- I tried to keep my powers a secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.75,0:12:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But as you know, it wasn't enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.42,0:12:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I owe my life to my\Ntraining, and my Semblance.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.96,0:12:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,At the end of the day, those are still
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.25,0:12:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,your most powerful tools.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.25,0:12:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,- What is your Semblance?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.13,0:12:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,- Preflexes! A silly name I came up with.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.21,0:13:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Hard to explain, but I can\Nsense everything better
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.00,0:13:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,than most and react to attacks\Nalmost before they happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.38,0:13:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Combine that with my\Ntraining and secret ability
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.67,0:13:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to turn Grimm to stone, or blind them,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.04,0:13:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,or vaporize them. (clears throat)
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.96,0:13:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's how you become the Grimm Reaper!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.71,0:13:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,- So, how do I laser beam\Nmonsters with my eyeballs?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.67,0:13:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- First, you stop thinking like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.25,0:13:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to think of all\Nthe times you've triggered
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.75,0:13:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,your powers. What did those\Nmoments have in common?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.46,0:13:42.75,Default,,0,0,0,,- I was scared, and stressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.04,0:13:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it emotional? Like\Nunlocking a Semblance?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.13,0:13:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,- It's emotional, but\Nmore focused than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.71,0:13:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Think, what is it you wanted?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.08,0:13:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,- I wanted to protect my friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.75,0:14:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- Precisely! It is the\Ndesire to preserve life
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.96,0:14:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,which fuels the light inside you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.71,0:14:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And to make no mistake, it is light.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.25,0:14:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Preservation is an extension of creation,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.54,0:14:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,or, at the very least,\Nan enemy of destruction.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.08,0:14:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The Creatures of Grimm were\Nmade by the God of Darkness,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.88,0:14:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,but your light comes from his brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.04,0:14:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,- How do you know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.21,0:14:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,- I always knew how to use the light,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.42,0:14:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,but never why it only worked on the Grimm.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.79,0:14:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, Jinn showed us her vision.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.13,0:14:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Were you paying attention?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.13,0:14:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,- The God of Light...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.33,0:14:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,His eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.25,0:14:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, where do we start?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.04,0:14:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,- Well, not here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.04,0:15:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The light will only work\Nin the presence of Grimm.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.33,0:15:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Meaning the only practice you'll get
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.54,0:15:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,will be a trial by fire.\NBut, what you can do
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.25,0:15:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,is focus on creating a state of mind
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.79,0:15:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that you can tap into when you need it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.92,0:15:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't think about your light as a means
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.46,0:15:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,of destroying evil, but as a way
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.46,0:15:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,to protect the people of Remnant.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.13,0:15:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,- But that can't be right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.92,0:15:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,- Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.50,0:15:29.54,Default,,0,0,0,,- You said the light only\Nreacts to Grimm, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.13,0:15:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I used it during our battle at Haven.\NIt reacted to Cinder.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.04,0:15:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,- Interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.75,0:15:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps there was something\Nthat you just weren't seeing?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.29,0:15:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,- Ruby!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.67,0:15:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,- Oh, hey guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.54,0:15:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,- What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.25,0:15:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,- It's Oscar.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.08,0:15:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He's missing.
